<li id="cite_note-wolf-6"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-wolf_6-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-wolf_6-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-wolf_6-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-wolf_6-3"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-wolf_6-4"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFWolf2009" class="citation book cs1">Wolf, Martin (2009). "<i>passim</i>, esp chp 3". <span class="id-lock-registration" title="Free registration required"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/fixingglobalfina0000wolf"><i>Fixing Global Finance</i></a></span>. Yale University Press.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=passim%2C+esp+chp+3&amp;rft.btitle=Fixing+Global+Finance&amp;rft.pub=Yale+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2009&amp;rft.aulast=Wolf&amp;rft.aufirst=Martin&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Ffixingglobalfina0000wolf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACapital+account" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-7"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">However, in late 2011 China also had periods when it was selling foreign reserves to prevent depreciation, this was due to surges of funds leaving the country through the private sector component of the capital account.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-8"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">
<cite id="CITEREFSweta_C._SaxenaKar-yiu_Wong1999" class="citation web cs1">Sweta C. Saxena; Kar-yiu Wong (1999-01-02). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://faculty.washington.edu/karyiu/papers/crisis-sur.pdf">"Currency Crises and Capital Controls: A Selective Survey"</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span>. <a href="/wiki/University_of_Washington" title="University of Washington">University of Washington</a><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2009-12-16</span></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Currency+Crises+and+Capital+Controls%3A+A+Selective+Survey&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Washington&amp;rft.date=1999-01-02&amp;rft.au=Sweta+C.+Saxena&amp;rft.au=Kar-yiu+Wong&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Ffaculty.washington.edu%2Fkaryiu%2Fpapers%2Fcrisis-sur.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACapital+account" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-9"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">
<cite id="CITEREFJ._Onno_de_Beaufort_Wijnholds_and_Lars_Søndergaard2007" class="citation web cs1">J. Onno de Beaufort Wijnholds and Lars Søndergaard (2007-09-16). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.ecb.int/pub/pdf/scpops/ecbocp73.pdf">"RESERVE ACCUMULATION - Objective or by-product?"</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span>. <a href="/wiki/European_Central_Bank" title="European Central Bank">ECB</a><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2009-12-16</span></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=RESERVE+ACCUMULATION+-+Objective+or+by-product%3F&amp;rft.pub=ECB&amp;rft.date=2007-09-16&amp;rft.au=J.+Onno+de+Beaufort+Wijnholds+and+Lars+S%C3%B8ndergaard&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ecb.int%2Fpub%2Fpdf%2Fscpops%2Fecbocp73.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACapital+account" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-10"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Though with a few exceptions, e.g. <i>International economics</i> by Krugman and Obstfeld which uses the IMF definition in at least its 5th edition.</span>
</li>
